  "body": "### Reproduction\r\n\r\nCreate a `script.js` file with this content:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nlet a = []\r\n\r\nfor (let i = 1; i < 1_000_000; i++) {\r\n  a.push(\"foo\".repeat(1_000_000))\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis file can be run with `node index.js` but throws an OOM error if you run it with `node --max-old-space-size=100`.\r\n\r\nOn the other hand, both `hh run index.js` and `hh run --max-memory 100 index.js` work.\r\n\r\n`NODE_OPTIONS=\"--max-old-space-size=100\" hh run index.js` does work and throws an OOM.",
